# GLB preview — authored transform (Blender export)

**Policy:** All catalog / telemetry / Sensor Studio **GLB preview** viewports keep the glTF root **position, rotation, and scale** from the Blender export. Do **not** reintroduce host-side “helpful” framing unless explicitly requested.

## Default

| Constant | Value | File |
|----------|--------|------|
| `GLB_PREVIEW_BODY_PLACEMENT_MODE` | **`authored`** | `extension/src/webview/bitstream-app/components/3d-rotation/shared/rotationPreviewConstants.ts` |

## Mount pattern

- Use **`GlbPreviewModelRoot`** (`components/3d-rotation/shared/GlbPreviewModelRoot.tsx`) or **`<primitive object={scene} />`** on the cached **`useGLTF` scene**.
- **Do not clone** skinned GLBs for display — clones break animation bindings (documented in rotation preview + animation lab).

## Do not (unless user asks or catalog override)

| Anti-pattern | Why |
|--------------|-----|
| `Box3.getCenter()` → `position.sub(center)` on load | Sinks top-heavy models (e.g. Tesa Drone) below the grid |
| Uniform **`0.5`** scale wrapper (`ROTATION_PREVIEW_BODY_GLB_SCALE` was legacy) | Ignores export scale |
| **`BOARD_GROUP_POSITION_Y`** offset on body mesh | Ignores export pivot |
| drei **`<Center>`** around preview GLBs | Auto-recenter |
| **`centerObjectToOrigin`** after `GLTFLoader.load` | Same as bbox center (Model Viewer) |
| Thumbnail pipeline mutating **`root.position` / `root.scale`** | Frame **camera** to bbox instead |

**OK:** Camera / orbit **target** from bounding sphere **without** moving the model (`frameCameraToObject`, `FitCameraToModel`).

## Optional overrides

1. **Global integrator:** set `GLB_PREVIEW_BODY_PLACEMENT_MODE` to `bbox-floor` or `bbox-center` (`compute-glb-preview-body-placement.ts`).
2. **Per asset:** catalog sidecar `animationLab.transform` — see **`extension/src/webview/bitstream-app/components/animation-lab/ANIMATION_LAB_CATALOG_METADATA.md`**.

## Surfaces using this policy

- Animation Lab — `components/animation-lab/`
- Rotation / quaternion preview — `RotationPreviewBodyGlb`, `OrientationMarkerMesh`
- Sensor Studio Model Viewer — `RotationPreviewPanelV4.tsx` (no load-time center)
- Model Loader R3F preview, Model Catalog modal (camera-only fit)
- Simulation GLB stubs — `SimulationModelScene`, E84 / ABB scenes (no `<Center>`)

## Out of scope (different requirements)

- **Vehicle physics** — may center clones for Jolt colliders; not catalog preview policy.
- **Procedural fallbacks** — e.g. `GlbMissingTesaiotFallback` may center generated geometry.

